SUMMARY:Invasive Removal (Marvin)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Habitat Builders Chapter for a community volunteer effort to restore forested areas by removing invasive plants. Volunteers will be working together to remove invasive underbrush and improve the health and appearance of shared natural spaces. This is a great opportunity to give back to the community while learning from a local expert. We are pleased to have Kristyna Culp of Habitat Builders joining us to provide a brief training session before the work begins. Whether you can stay for an hour or the entire morning\, your help will make a meaningful difference! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/invasive-removal-marvin/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/habitatbuilders.jpg
END:VEVENT
