SUMMARY:Invasive Plant Removal at Purser-Hulsey Park (Matthews)
DESCRIPTION:Join HAWK for a hands-on morning of conservation as we continue our successful effort to remove invasive plants at Purser-Hulsey Park! Together we’ll tackle Kudzu\, Wisteria\, and Blackberry helping native plants and wildlife thrive. There will be two volunteer times available: 10 am – 1 pm and 2 pm – 5 pm. \nPlease wear long pants and long sleeves\, and bring gloves\, water\, and pruning tools (pruners\, loppers\, etc.). We’ll have some extra tools available on site. \nCome lend a hand\, enjoy the outdoors\, and make a real difference for our local habitat! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/invasive-plant-removal-at-purser-hulsey-park-matthews/
CATEGORIES:Featured
END:VEVENT
