SUMMARY:Family Bird Walk (Durham)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Durham Wildlife Stewards Chapter and the New Hope Bird Alliance for a guided bird walk in Sandy Creek Park. We will meander through the park\, pointing out the many birds in the air\, on the ground\, or in their nests as we walk. This is mating and nesting season\, and birdsong will be in the air all around us! \nBring binoculars and a bird field guide or app if you have them. Wear shoes that could get muddy. No dogs\, please.\n \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/family-bird-walk-durham/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/birdwalk.jpg
END:VEVENT
