SUMMARY:City Nature Challenge (Concord)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Concord Wildlife Alliance Chapter for a fun and educational outing as we participate in the City Nature Challenge! The City Nature Challenge is a global community science event where people document local plants\, animals\, and fungi to help scientists better understand and protect biodiversity. We’ll explore Frank Liske Park\, observe wildlife\, and upload our findings to the iNaturalist app. Please make sure to download iNaturalist on your phone ahead of time so you’re ready to help document the incredible biodiversity in our community. We can’t wait to explore with you! This is a family friendly program! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/city-nature-challenge-concord/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/CityNatureChallenge.jpg
END:VEVENT
